<br>
Currently I'm level 29, and I am still wearing the same newbie quest armor (except the robe), a few cloth pieces, and a couple of items I got in auction very cheaply, I have all my level 29 spells, and still over 300pp to spare.<br>
<br>
For a mage, what you wear is of so little importance. Your pet and your (you, the player's) ability will carry you along, not your equipment. Until you can get to the highest levels of the game, your pet will be no stronger (except with the Sol Ro quests after L34), your nukes no better, nor your mana return any faster than the player with thousands of plat worth of gear. You are 95% as effective with no gear as you are fully equipped (as long as you have 1 piece of malachite for a pet).<br>
<br>
The best advice is to do the newbie quests for your basic equipment, use your cash for your spells (they are all that will make a difference) and add new and better items as you learn the game.<br>
<br>
The best tradeskill to get into as a mage with no money is tailoring, and high level tailors are among the wealhiest EQ players. You can start at level one in Ak'anon, buy sewing ket (large if you can afford it) and start with spiderling silks. As you move out into Lesser Feydark or Butcherblock, you can find giant spiders and make raw silk armor to fill in those pieces not covered by quest armor. Check out eqtaders for more information as you learn your craft. <p>Yisaar, Iksar Reaver<BR>
